node.text: The @ryandungeyfoundation ‘Opportunity Awaits Ride Day’ at Fox Raceway is this Saturday. To help raise funds, we’ve created an online fundraising team to help support (link in bio to join or donate to my team). I challenge @jettson18 to create a fundraising team and to beat our team in collected donations. Let’s GO TEAM94!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ken Roczen on September 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, motorcycle and outdoors.

node.text:
The season is done! What a tough break. My foot got stuck in a wheel on the start in the second moto.

I instantly though my foot was broken. My boot buckle got pushed through the boot and into my foot and that was the end of that. It’s not broken luckily. With 2x 0 points this year (Millville moto 1, Hangtown moto 2) i lost 2nd place in the championship 😩

I m keeping my head high though. Being in the title hunt in SX and MX is still special to me so overall i feel like i had a pretty good season and made a step forward from the past years.

Big thank you and congrats to my team @honda_racing_us for giving me the support and also for winning the 250 outdoor championship with @jettson18

@jordantroxell  thank you for doing what you do and always having my back ! 🙏🏼🤘🏽

Time to get some rest and relax before we prepare for 2022. Thank you to all the fans this year it was an awesome feeling to have you guys back. ❤️

📸 @j_reedphotos

node.text:
Big congratulations to @dylanferrandis and his team. You guys did a great job this year and were super tough to beat. Good job again for a strong outdoor season.

My weekend was not very good. I haven’t been feeling quite right and it was very noticeable yesterday.
I felt weak yesterday and with the weather it was just a suffer fest from practice to racing. I tried a late moto charge in the first moto and ended up throwing up.
I have a history of fainting when i throw up so i slowed down completely until it was all out and then i pushed again in the last lap to secure 3rd.

Second moto was just straight misery. Ended 6th in that moto. Glad i was able to minimize the damage and score some points.
